s use stun to taunt all the time.  All the time, including vs. unstunnable mobs.  Notably, vs. Shrooms and Juggs in Seb and Kael Giants (I usually group with them as my shaman in these areas).<br><br>I don't think the SoD was nerfed aggro wise.  I think you're just stuck with some extra spam which you have to deal with if you have one. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ubromsots.showPublicProfile?language=EN>BromSotS</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 51<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/9/02 1:24:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1768.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   .</span><hr size=1> I use dual SoD's. Basically its the ultimate tauting tool. and now that the spell can land on a lot of high level mobs, its working even better. the stun gets resisted a lot, but hey, at 12/18 and a 288 DD every few seconds, who cares. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uwandork.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wandor K</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>/con's RED</span><br>  Posts: 307<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/9/02 1:37:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1768.topic&index=20>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Sceptre of Destruction Nerf</span><hr size=1> the reason people are calling this a nerf Hellra1ser is because VI changed the way the code works.<br><br>The old way:<br>Giants are unstunnable so they raised their MR to be really high. No magic based spells land ever. Same with mez and slow. They just cranked the MR to a super high level so the spells would never land.<br><br>The new way:<br>VI added code to allow tagging a mob as immune to certain types of spells. Now rather than an unslowable mob being totally MR, it has reasonable resists but it will give a message that a mob is not slowable. Other types of spells land, just not the ones that VI tagged on that particular mob.<br><br>The reason that its somewhat of a nerf is that a resisted spell still generates as much agro as one that lands. In the case of unstunnable mob, rather than just having the Anarchy proc resisted and generating a ton of agro, it just bounces the stun portion and the DD still has a chance to land. The problem being that the stun is not resisted and generating agro - it just doesn't go through, you get a message saying the mob is immune to stun. <p><div align="center" style="font-size: 11px; font-family: arial"><img src="http://www.bfdesigns.net/eq/wandor_sig.jpg"><br><a target="_blank" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6103"><b>Wandor's profile</b></a> | <a target="_blank" href="http://www.exarch.net/"><b>Fusion of Flame</b></a> | <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6102" target="_blank"><b>Moordian's profile</b></a></div></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showMessageRange?topicID=1768.topic&start=21&stop=22>2</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showPrevMessage?topicID=1768.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showNextMessage?topicID=1768.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://p